title: Millburn High School Varsity Club Athletes of the Week
text:
Millburn High School Varsity Club Athletes of the Week October 14, 2015 Last updated: Wednesday, October 14, 2015, 3:40 PM The Item of Millburn and Short Hills Print 
The boys cross country team, the girls cross country team and harriers Matt Grossman and Katie Delidow are the recipients of Millburn High School Varsity Club Athlete of the Week honors for Oct. 5-11. 
The boys cross country team captured a fifth consecutive Super Essex Conference, American Division championship meet crown Oct. 6 at Branch Brook Park in Newark with 34 points, 39 points in front of runner-up Columbia High School. 
The squad's top five runners averaged 16:38.7, the second fastest time in course history. 
Millburn's girls cross country team claimed its first ever American Division championship meet title with a 49-63 defeat of 2014 titlist Montclair High School. 
Grossman, a junior, ran a meet record 15:41.9 to repeat as the American Division boys champion. 
Delidow, also a junior, crossed the finish in 18:57.5 to become the first Millburn female to capture an American Division championship race crown. Â© 2015 North Jersey Media Group Tags:
